Seventh Edition Unix (V7), released in 1979, is the common ancestor of both BSD and System V. The Bourne Shell first appeared in V7, replacing the earlier Thompson Shell. If your script needs to work on pre-POSIX Unix systems, the features of V7 are a good portability target, as they represent the least common denominator of nearly all extant Unices. A full tree of V7, including source and manpages, may be found at http://min
